They would have been fortunate to get through, however, and neither Rodgers or Gerrard were looking to make excuses.

‘The big game was away in Basle where we did not play well (and lost 1-0),’ said Rodgers. ‘We have no complaints. If you deserve to go through, you go through. We have not been good enough to go through. We have to take it on the chin.

‘When you don’t qualify everyone gets looked upon. We wanted to qualify. We have been analysed and for us the solution is we have to do better – manager and players – the expectancy was high but this is a different group of players and squad.’ 

